== What? ==

Thumbslug is a content/entitlement proxy.

== How? ==

To run, use `buildr serve`, or `java -jar target/thumbslug-1.0.0.jar`

To run via jsvc (experimental):

/usr/bin/jsvc -debug -cp thumbslug-1.0.0.jar org.candlepin.thumbslug.Daemon

^^ specifying the full path to jsvc is important, it examines argv[0]

== Config Options ==

port = <integer>       :: the local address to listen for requests on
ssl = <true|false>     :: use ssl for client to thumbslug communication

cdn.port = <integer>   :: the remote cdn port to connect to
cdn.host = <string>    :: hostname of the cdn
cdn.ssl = <true|false> :: use ssl for connecting to the cdn

